1
00:00:29,007 --> 00:00:31,027
Back in Graycastle,

2
00:00:31,027 --> 00:00:35,267
Fourth Prince Roland Wimbledon 
was already notorious.

3
00:00:35,267 --> 00:00:37,767
A life of debauchery, utter incompetence,

4
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:41,297
not a shred of noble grace... 
the list goes on.

5
00:00:41,297 --> 00:00:45,957
Compared to his four siblings, 
he was worlds apart.

6
00:00:45,957 --> 00:00:51,007
Ah, why was I sent to assist 
him in the Royal Decree?

7
00:00:51,007 --> 00:00:53,997
If His Majesty hadn't promised 
to appoint me as the

8
00:00:53,997 --> 00:00:56,567
official Finance Minister once 
the Royal Decree concluded,

9
00:00:56,567 --> 00:00:59,447
I wouldn't have come to 
this godforsaken place.

10
00:00:59,447 --> 00:01:02,707
And yet, things began to change.

11
00:01:02,707 --> 00:01:05,857
When exactly did it start?

12
00:01:06,377 --> 00:01:11,227
Probably around the time 
he saved that witch.

13
00:01:11,227 --> 00:01:15,707
His Highness Roland displayed a 
sharp mind and grand strategic vision.

14
00:01:15,707 --> 00:01:17,997
He skillfully avoided his own predicament,

15
00:01:17,997 --> 00:01:20,717
and struck at the very 
essence of theocracy.

16
00:01:20,717 --> 00:01:25,607
By using witches, he set his sights 
directly on the Church of Hermes.

17
00:01:25,607 --> 00:01:29,287
At first, I thought it was 
just baseless rhetoric.

18
00:01:29,287 --> 00:01:32,447
But then, His Highness spent all night 
studying financial reports,

19
00:01:32,447 --> 00:01:34,137
formulating trade strategies,

20
00:01:34,137 --> 00:01:37,607
and even proposed something 
called the "Silk Road."

21
00:01:37,607 --> 00:01:40,847
Heaven knows where he learned those words.

22
00:01:40,847 --> 00:01:43,237
Still, to possess such a long-term vision,

23
00:01:43,237 --> 00:01:47,567
while keeping his focus squarely on the 
immediate development of Border Town,

24
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:50,407
this is no baseless fantasy.

25
00:01:50,407 --> 00:01:53,857
But if we cannot survive 
the Months of Demons,

26
00:01:53,857 --> 00:01:56,827
everything will be for nothing.

27
00:01:56,827 --> 00:02:01,737
I hear from Carter that His Highness 
now plans to build a city wall.

28
00:02:01,737 --> 00:02:04,877
Winter is just over three months away.

29
00:02:04,877 --> 00:02:08,847
Even if it's only around 2000 feet long, 
it should be theoretically impossible.

30
00:02:08,847 --> 00:02:12,237
But His Highness has already 
surprised me so many times.

31
00:02:12,237 --> 00:02:13,577
There's still three months left.

32
00:02:13,577 --> 00:02:17,737
If it really can't be done, 
there's still time to run away.

33
00:02:17,737 --> 00:02:22,827
How will His Highness build a 
city wall in just three months?

34
00:02:22,827 --> 00:02:26,507
From here on, things are only 
getting more interesting.

35
00:04:38,397 --> 00:04:40,507
Be careful. Move it over there.

36
00:04:48,337 --> 00:04:51,407
Go to the North Mountain mine and 
bring back a cartload of limestone.

37
00:04:51,407 --> 00:04:53,857
Also get a cartload of clay, 
something like this.

38
00:04:54,757 --> 00:04:58,037
Then have someone crush them into 
small pieces, mix them thoroughly,

39
00:04:58,037 --> 00:05:00,647
and spread the mixture evenly 
in the pit in the firing room.

40
00:05:07,457 --> 00:05:10,027
Leave the rest to Miss Anna.

41
00:05:41,257 --> 00:05:44,087
Carter, get someone to 
crush this clinker.

42
00:05:44,087 --> 00:05:46,797
Mix it with gypsum at a 10:1 
ratio and grind it into powder.

43
00:05:46,797 --> 00:05:49,277
Your Highness, what is this for?

44
00:05:50,567 --> 00:05:52,277
A new formula from the alchemy workshop.

45
00:05:54,597 --> 00:05:56,927
Your Highness, everything is 
prepared as you instructed.

46
00:05:57,727 --> 00:05:59,347
What exactly are you making?

47
00:06:05,207 --> 00:06:09,227
Miss Anna, this time, 
let me show you a bit of magic.

48
00:06:09,537 --> 00:06:11,727
Your Highness, you can use magic too?

49
00:06:13,647 --> 00:06:16,567
Yes. A kind of magic called science.

50
00:06:16,567 --> 00:06:17,647
Science?

51
00:06:17,647 --> 00:06:21,927
Carter, mix this powder with water 
and pour it onto those stones over there.

52
00:06:21,927 --> 00:06:25,467
Pour it into the gaps, so that it's 
evenly spread between the stones.

53
00:06:25,467 --> 00:06:28,527
By tomorrow, they will 
become a solid wall.

54
00:06:28,527 --> 00:06:31,127
Huh? You must be joking!

55
00:06:31,127 --> 00:06:32,977
Miss Anna, do you believe me?

56
00:06:34,677 --> 00:06:36,977
Whatever you say, I believe you.

57
00:06:38,207 --> 00:06:39,477
Then do as I say.

58
00:06:39,477 --> 00:06:41,107
Let's wait and see.

59
00:06:41,927 --> 00:06:44,407
Y-Yes, Your Highness.

60
00:06:55,127 --> 00:06:56,267
Go on, Carter.

61
00:06:56,847 --> 00:06:58,307
Test its strength.

62
00:07:15,497 --> 00:07:17,647
T-This is truly incredible, Your Highness.

63
00:07:18,197 --> 00:07:21,187
With this, we can build our 
city wall as fast as we want.

64
00:07:21,187 --> 00:07:24,147
A border wall in five years 
would be well within reach.

65
00:07:24,147 --> 00:07:26,167
We could even use it to 
reinforce this castle,

66
00:07:26,167 --> 00:07:29,347
making it the strongest, 
safest castle in Graycastle.

67
00:07:29,347 --> 00:07:30,587
Not just the castle.

68
00:07:30,587 --> 00:07:32,647
We'll use it to build much more.

69
00:07:32,997 --> 00:07:34,447
Much more?

70
00:07:40,397 --> 00:07:42,957
Could I have ten thousand mansions,

71
00:07:42,957 --> 00:07:46,397
sheltering all the poor scholars 
and making them rejoice.

72
00:07:47,287 --> 00:07:49,117
Your Highness, what did you say?

73
00:07:50,087 --> 00:07:53,897
We'll use it to build a 
better home for everyone.

74
00:07:54,627 --> 00:07:57,127
Everyone can live in a sturdy house,

75
00:07:57,127 --> 00:07:59,897
one that neither storms 
nor blizzards can destroy.

76
00:08:01,847 --> 00:08:04,517
Miss Anna, starting today,

77
00:08:04,517 --> 00:08:06,267
please fire a batch every day.

78
00:08:06,827 --> 00:08:08,397
Yes, Your Highness.

79
00:08:09,267 --> 00:08:12,107
Carter, you're in charge 
of wall construction.

80
00:08:12,107 --> 00:08:14,117
Make sure it's built within three months.

81
00:08:14,117 --> 00:08:15,277
Yes, Your Highness.

82
00:08:15,277 --> 00:08:16,337
Leave it to me.

83
00:08:22,297 --> 00:08:24,527
Oh, by the way, Your Highness,

84
00:08:24,527 --> 00:08:27,397
what is this miraculous 
alchemical powder called?

85
00:08:31,447 --> 00:08:32,467
Cement.

86
00:08:38,397 --> 00:08:40,727
What... What is this?

87
00:08:48,407 --> 00:08:49,937
What's going on?

88
00:08:49,937 --> 00:08:51,117
So many days have passed.

89
00:08:51,117 --> 00:08:53,057
Why is construction moving so slowly?

90
00:08:53,057 --> 00:08:54,897
And it's crooked and uneven.

91
00:08:54,897 --> 00:08:56,457
You can't even stand on it properly.

92
00:08:56,457 --> 00:08:58,007
Forget holding off demonic beasts,

93
00:08:58,007 --> 00:08:59,147
it'd collapse in the first rain.

94
00:08:59,147 --> 00:09:00,397
Apologies, Your Highness.

95
00:09:00,397 --> 00:09:01,687
It is my responsibility.

96
00:09:03,127 --> 00:09:05,367
Your Highness, if I may speak frankly,

97
00:09:05,367 --> 00:09:08,097
Carter has no prior 
experience in such matters.

98
00:09:08,097 --> 00:09:10,027
For a wall over 2000 feet long,

99
00:09:10,027 --> 00:09:13,847
without an experienced architect 
to oversee the work,

100
00:09:13,847 --> 00:09:18,867
even with this miraculous 
alchemical agent called "cement,"

101
00:09:18,867 --> 00:09:21,687
it would be difficult to meet 
Your Highness's expectations.

102
00:09:22,097 --> 00:09:25,707
We need a true master stonemason.

103
00:09:25,707 --> 00:09:26,977
A master stonemason...

104
00:09:28,727 --> 00:09:31,367
Go and recruit one immediately, 
no matter the cost.

105
00:09:31,367 --> 00:09:34,427
But Your Highness, 
it's not a matter of money.

106
00:09:34,427 --> 00:09:38,567
There's no one with this kind 
of expertise in Border Town.

107
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:41,417
Then look for one in 
Longsong Stronghold or Willow Town.

108
00:09:41,417 --> 00:09:44,307
Even if you have to go back 
to Graycastle, find someone.

109
00:10:25,687 --> 00:10:26,997
Professor Karl!

110
00:10:30,707 --> 00:10:31,857
I...

111
00:10:32,847 --> 00:10:33,857
I've become...

112
00:10:35,427 --> 00:10:37,857
I've become a witch too.

113
00:10:40,867 --> 00:10:43,687
Mr. van Bate, could you 
please come over here?

114
00:10:48,577 --> 00:10:49,487
What's happened?

115
00:10:49,487 --> 00:10:51,507
Please take a look at this notice for us.

116
00:10:51,507 --> 00:10:53,477
They say the prince posted it.

117
00:10:53,477 --> 00:10:55,357
What does it say?

118
00:10:55,357 --> 00:10:57,137
By decree of Roland Wimbledon,

119
00:10:57,137 --> 00:10:59,107
Fourth Prince of
the Kingdom of Graycastle:

120
00:10:59,107 --> 00:11:01,567
Urgent recruitment for 
the following positions:

121
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:06,397
Stonebreakers: male, 
ages 20 - 40, physically strong.

122
00:11:06,397 --> 00:11:08,487
Daily wage: 25 bronze royals.

123
00:11:08,487 --> 00:11:12,627
Masons: Any gender, 
ages 18+, with masonry experience.

124
00:11:12,627 --> 00:11:14,787
Daily wage: 45 bronze royals.

125
00:11:14,787 --> 00:11:17,907
Laborers: male, ages 18+.

126
00:11:17,907 --> 00:11:19,877
Daily wage: 12 bronze royals.

127
00:11:19,877 --> 00:11:22,997
Master stonemasons: Any gender, any age.

128
00:11:22,997 --> 00:11:24,947
Must have experience in 
municipal construction,

129
00:11:24,947 --> 00:11:27,527
fortress building, 
or large-scale engineering projects.

130
00:11:27,527 --> 00:11:29,407
Monthly wage: 1 gold royal.

131
00:11:29,407 --> 00:11:31,437
Those with exceptional 
experience and performance

132
00:11:31,437 --> 00:11:32,787
may be granted official positions.

133
00:11:32,787 --> 00:11:36,357
Fourth Prince of the 
Kingdom of Graycastle, Roland Wimbledon.

134
00:11:36,357 --> 00:11:37,327
Did I hear that right?

135
00:11:37,327 --> 00:11:39,127
You could even become an official,

136
00:11:39,127 --> 00:11:41,357
maybe see His Highness 
the Prince every day!

137
00:11:42,337 --> 00:11:44,437
Mr. van Bate, Mr. van Bate!

138
00:11:47,287 --> 00:11:49,837
A master stonemason came 
to apply so quickly?

139
00:11:49,837 --> 00:11:51,857
Didn't you say finding one would be hard?

140
00:11:51,857 --> 00:11:53,447
I'm surprised too.

141
00:11:53,447 --> 00:11:55,827
The man is clearly a local teacher,

142
00:11:55,827 --> 00:11:59,537
yet he claims to have experience 
in large-scale construction projects.

143
00:11:59,537 --> 00:12:01,737
Your Highness, would you like to see him?

144
00:12:02,887 --> 00:12:05,057
Of course. Bring him in.

145
00:12:05,687 --> 00:12:07,857
So you're here to apply 
as master stonemason?

146
00:12:07,857 --> 00:12:09,287
Yes, Your Highness.

147
00:12:09,287 --> 00:12:11,907
My name is Karl van Bate.

148
00:12:11,907 --> 00:12:14,857
I heard you used to teach in town.

149
00:12:14,857 --> 00:12:17,987
I just taught the children to recognize 
their names, Your Highness.

150
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:19,897
Then what qualifies you for this position?

151
00:12:19,897 --> 00:12:24,697
I... have participated in the maintenance 
of embankments within Graycastle,

152
00:12:24,697 --> 00:12:26,357
the design and construction of the palace,

153
00:12:26,357 --> 00:12:29,357
and the renovation of 
various public facilities.

154
00:12:30,587 --> 00:12:34,437
You mean you've been involved in many 
major construction projects in Graycastle?

155
00:12:35,157 --> 00:12:37,437
Yes, Your Highness.

156
00:12:37,437 --> 00:12:39,977
All large-scale construction in Graycastle

157
00:12:39,977 --> 00:12:42,267
is handled by the Mason Guild.

158
00:12:42,267 --> 00:12:45,187
Are you a member of the 
Graycastle Mason Guild?

159
00:12:46,417 --> 00:12:48,207
Yes, Your Highness.

160
00:12:49,017 --> 00:12:51,027
The Mason Guild's members 
are naturally elites.

161
00:12:51,027 --> 00:12:54,117
But as I recall, during construction of 
the Graycastle Theater a few years ago,

162
00:12:54,117 --> 00:12:55,977
a collapse occurred.

163
00:12:55,977 --> 00:12:57,937
The entire Mason Guild was convicted

164
00:12:57,937 --> 00:12:59,227
and executed.

165
00:13:01,467 --> 00:13:04,157
That is indeed how the 
story spread outside.

166
00:13:04,157 --> 00:13:06,697
Oh? Then what really happened?

167
00:13:07,227 --> 00:13:09,157
The administrator at the time,

168
00:13:09,157 --> 00:13:11,267
for a kickback of several 
hundred gold royals,

169
00:13:11,267 --> 00:13:13,167
ordered us to switch the stone,

170
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:15,247
which led to the accident.

171
00:13:15,247 --> 00:13:17,767
We warned the administrator 
many times that

172
00:13:17,767 --> 00:13:21,727
using that grade of stone would 
compromise structural integrity.

173
00:13:21,727 --> 00:13:23,657
But no one listened.

174
00:13:23,657 --> 00:13:25,287
After the accident,

175
00:13:25,287 --> 00:13:28,167
we explained everything 
to the investigators.

176
00:13:28,167 --> 00:13:31,677
But the official who 
ordered the substitution

177
00:13:31,677 --> 00:13:33,517
claimed that it was to save costs.

178
00:13:34,087 --> 00:13:37,977
In the end, he was deemed to have 
good intentions and was acquitted.

179
00:13:37,977 --> 00:13:41,757
The entire Mason Guild 
was sentenced to death.

180
00:13:42,357 --> 00:13:45,357
I heard rumors beforehand 
and fled overnight.

181
00:13:45,357 --> 00:13:48,227
I came to Border Town 
and have hidden my identity ever since.

182
00:13:48,837 --> 00:13:50,727
If you've been hiding your identity,

183
00:13:50,727 --> 00:13:53,227
why are you revealing yourself 
and applying for the job now?

184
00:13:54,047 --> 00:13:57,607
Because...  I have a reason 
I can no longer stay silent.

185
00:13:57,607 --> 00:13:58,627
What reason?

186
00:13:59,487 --> 00:14:00,117
I...

187
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:02,857
I'm sorry, Your Highness.

188
00:14:02,857 --> 00:14:05,227
I cannot yet reveal my reason.

189
00:14:05,617 --> 00:14:06,517
Your Highness,

190
00:14:07,917 --> 00:14:10,147
I know you have doubts about me.

191
00:14:10,467 --> 00:14:13,867
After all, I defied the investigation 
and fled, a capital offense.

192
00:14:13,867 --> 00:14:15,697
But I really had no choice.

193
00:14:15,697 --> 00:14:18,037
If I hadn't fled, 
I wouldn't be alive today.

194
00:14:18,607 --> 00:14:20,287
I've been a stonemason my whole life.

195
00:14:20,287 --> 00:14:22,067
I can definitely meet your requirements.

196
00:14:22,067 --> 00:14:25,177
Please give me a chance 
to atone for my sins.

197
00:14:28,987 --> 00:14:30,687
Barov, what do you think?

198
00:14:30,687 --> 00:14:35,277
Your Highness, I believe this 
man is mostly telling the truth.

199
00:14:35,277 --> 00:14:39,227
By law, he is now a fugitive 
guilty of a crime.

200
00:14:39,227 --> 00:14:42,967
However, considering your 
current needs, Your Highness,

201
00:14:43,627 --> 00:14:47,137
I think it would be wise 
to make an exception.

202
00:14:50,787 --> 00:14:54,187
Mr. van Bate, I pardon your crimes 
and appoint you as Master Stonemason.

203
00:14:54,187 --> 00:14:57,327
From now on, you're a member 
of the administrative office.

204
00:14:57,327 --> 00:15:00,317
Show me what a master 
from the Mason Guild can do.

205
00:15:03,837 --> 00:15:05,747
I want to build a city wall here,

206
00:15:05,747 --> 00:15:07,877
from the Dragonspine Mountain 
to the Redwater River,

207
00:15:07,877 --> 00:15:09,977
roughly 2000 feet in length.

208
00:15:10,557 --> 00:15:12,307
Fifteen feet high, six feet wide,

209
00:15:12,307 --> 00:15:14,457
wide enough for four men to walk abreast.

210
00:15:14,457 --> 00:15:16,567
Well? How would you go about it?

211
00:15:17,357 --> 00:15:20,097
First, to stabilize the upper structure,

212
00:15:20,097 --> 00:15:22,017
we'll need to dig a trench one man deep.

213
00:15:22,017 --> 00:15:26,717
And if the top is six feet wide 
and the wall is 15 feet high,

214
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:29,227
then the base must be at 
least twice that width.

215
00:15:29,847 --> 00:15:31,747
If Your Highness provides me with 150 men,

216
00:15:31,747 --> 00:15:33,897
I can complete the trench in three months.

217
00:15:34,407 --> 00:15:37,107
The upper wall must be 
built with solid stone.

218
00:15:37,107 --> 00:15:39,627
Cutting and polishing the 
stone will take a lot of time.

219
00:15:39,627 --> 00:15:42,217
The whole project will probably 
take three years to complete.

220
00:15:46,477 --> 00:15:48,747
A ditch won't stop the demonic beasts.

221
00:15:48,747 --> 00:15:50,167
Stop the demonic beasts...

222
00:15:50,167 --> 00:15:51,987
You... You mean...

223
00:15:52,477 --> 00:15:56,497
Yes. I need to build a wall 
capable of holding back demonic beasts.

224
00:15:56,497 --> 00:15:59,787
Therefore, it must be completed before 
the Months of Demons arrive this year.

225
00:15:59,787 --> 00:16:00,607
Can it be done?

226
00:16:01,617 --> 00:16:04,607
Well, if that's the case...

227
00:16:05,617 --> 00:16:07,997
Then the wall doesn't need 
to be built that high.

228
00:16:08,607 --> 00:16:09,717
Like this...

229
00:16:10,587 --> 00:16:12,887
If the height is reduced to 12 feet,

230
00:16:12,887 --> 00:16:15,287
and the width reduced by a third,

231
00:16:15,287 --> 00:16:18,307
then the base width shrinks to 6 feet.

232
00:16:18,307 --> 00:16:20,837
We can dig the trench and 
build the wall simultaneously.

233
00:16:20,837 --> 00:16:24,027
If we increase the workforce to 200,

234
00:16:24,027 --> 00:16:28,687
the foundation could be dug 
in about a month and a half.

235
00:16:28,687 --> 00:16:30,097
But...

236
00:16:30,097 --> 00:16:31,027
But what?

237
00:16:32,017 --> 00:16:35,167
Building the wall requires 
a lot of cut stone.

238
00:16:35,167 --> 00:16:36,887
In such a short time,

239
00:16:36,887 --> 00:16:39,107
there's no way we can 
process enough stone.

240
00:16:39,107 --> 00:16:41,447
Even if we bought it from nearby towns,

241
00:16:41,447 --> 00:16:43,567
factoring in transport time,

242
00:16:43,567 --> 00:16:45,547
I'm afraid it's still...

243
00:16:45,547 --> 00:16:47,547
So if we had enough stone,

244
00:16:47,547 --> 00:16:49,827
you could build the wall 
within three months?

245
00:16:49,827 --> 00:16:51,687
I believe so, yes.

246
00:16:51,687 --> 00:16:52,387
But...

247
00:16:52,387 --> 00:16:53,847
Then you don't need to worry.

248
00:16:54,377 --> 00:16:56,567
Come with me. 
I'll show you something.

249
00:16:57,527 --> 00:16:59,167
Oh, okay.

250
00:17:04,297 --> 00:17:06,457
This is amazing.

251
00:17:06,457 --> 00:17:07,747
It's incredible!

252
00:17:08,777 --> 00:17:11,887
They... They've bonded so solidly.

253
00:17:12,647 --> 00:17:16,627
With this, it's like having stone 
blocks in any shape we need,

254
00:17:16,627 --> 00:17:18,787
without cutting or polishing.

255
00:17:22,177 --> 00:17:25,567
If we can eliminate the 
time-consuming step of processing stone,

256
00:17:25,567 --> 00:17:27,397
the speed of any construction project

257
00:17:27,397 --> 00:17:28,907
will reach an entirely new level.

258
00:17:28,907 --> 00:17:31,897
Well? With this, can you 
finish in three months?

259
00:17:31,897 --> 00:17:34,547
Yes. This substance is magnificent.

260
00:17:34,547 --> 00:17:37,047
Your Highness, what did 
you say it was called?

261
00:17:37,047 --> 00:17:37,807
Cement.

262
00:17:37,807 --> 00:17:39,977
Cement. I'll remember that.

263
00:17:39,977 --> 00:17:44,517
I can't believe the alchemy workshop 
developed something this amazing.

264
00:17:44,517 --> 00:17:48,197
I'll write you some detailed 
instructions on how to use cement.

265
00:17:48,197 --> 00:17:51,147
If you need anything else, 
speak with my assistant minister, Barov.

266
00:17:51,997 --> 00:17:53,257
Yes, Your Highness.

267
00:17:54,937 --> 00:17:58,487
Your Highness, actually, 
there's one more thing.

268
00:17:58,487 --> 00:17:59,997
Oh? What is it?

269
00:17:59,997 --> 00:18:01,017
It's...

270
00:18:04,947 --> 00:18:05,967
Anna!

271
00:18:08,577 --> 00:18:10,037
Professor Karl!

272
00:18:15,087 --> 00:18:18,847
So, he's the aforementioned Professor Karl.

273
00:18:18,847 --> 00:18:22,967
Yes, many of the town's children 
go to his house for lessons.

274
00:18:22,967 --> 00:18:24,627
He's really kind to us.

275
00:18:25,437 --> 00:18:29,447
I only told them stories 
and taught them a few words.

276
00:18:29,447 --> 00:18:32,537
Anna, I thought you were dead.

277
00:18:32,537 --> 00:18:35,617
I've been having nightmares 
these past few days.

278
00:18:35,617 --> 00:18:38,097
It's such a relief you're alive.

279
00:18:39,417 --> 00:18:40,067
I...

280
00:18:41,567 --> 00:18:44,067
Your Highness, thank you for your mercy.

281
00:18:44,407 --> 00:18:46,117
Don't be like that. Please get up.

282
00:18:47,107 --> 00:18:48,107
Your Highness...

283
00:18:48,107 --> 00:18:51,007
Mr. van Bate, to me,

284
00:18:51,007 --> 00:18:53,467
witches aren't the 
embodiment of the Devil.

285
00:18:53,467 --> 00:18:56,447
I certainly won't hunt them 
down as the Church commands.

286
00:18:56,447 --> 00:18:58,267
Miss Anna is innocent.

287
00:18:58,267 --> 00:18:59,797
Of course I'd never harm her.

288
00:18:59,797 --> 00:19:02,867
Your Highness, 
there's something I must tell you.

289
00:19:06,197 --> 00:19:08,067
Oh, what is it?

290
00:19:08,067 --> 00:19:10,867
Do you remember I mentioned earlier

291
00:19:10,867 --> 00:19:13,557
that I had my own reason 
for coming to apply?

292
00:19:13,557 --> 00:19:15,337
I didn't dare tell you then,

293
00:19:15,337 --> 00:19:19,047
but now, I'm certain I can.

294
00:19:19,047 --> 00:19:23,067
In this Border Town, 
there is another witch.

295
00:19:36,257 --> 00:19:37,687
How can this be?

296
00:19:38,277 --> 00:19:42,687
Even Nana... has become a witch too?

297
00:19:42,687 --> 00:19:45,657
Who would've thought that 
in this tiny Border Town,

298
00:19:45,657 --> 00:19:47,137
there would be two witches?

299
00:19:47,137 --> 00:19:48,647
If this were anywhere else,

300
00:19:48,647 --> 00:19:52,027
there would be another bloody witch hunt.

301
00:19:52,027 --> 00:19:57,287
But how will His Highness react here?

302
00:20:02,707 --> 00:20:05,687
This is what I wish to ask 
of you, Your Highness.

303
00:20:05,687 --> 00:20:08,427
Your Highness is merciful and 
unafraid of the rumors of the Devil.

304
00:20:08,427 --> 00:20:12,187
It's Anna's good fortune 
to be able to join your harem.

305
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:16,547
Although Nana is still 
young and cannot serve you,

306
00:20:16,547 --> 00:20:18,247
she is truly innocent.

307
00:20:18,247 --> 00:20:20,317
I beg you, Your Highness,

308
00:20:20,317 --> 00:20:21,687
please save her too.

309
00:20:23,177 --> 00:20:24,617
It's not what you think.

310
00:20:24,617 --> 00:20:27,367
I saved Anna because I need her help.

311
00:20:27,367 --> 00:20:29,847
I-I believe that once Nana grows up,

312
00:20:29,847 --> 00:20:31,687
she'll definitely be able to help you too.

313
00:20:34,677 --> 00:20:36,547
You truly misunderstand.

314
00:20:36,547 --> 00:20:41,187
Miss Anna's job is to make 
the cement I just showed you.

315
00:20:41,187 --> 00:20:42,197
What?

316
00:20:42,837 --> 00:20:46,187
That miraculous substance 
was actually made by Anna?

317
00:20:46,867 --> 00:20:48,417
As for this Nana you mentioned,

318
00:20:48,417 --> 00:20:49,767
I'd like to meet her.

319
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:51,707
I can guarantee her safety.

320
00:20:51,707 --> 00:20:53,037
Could you bring her to me?

321
00:20:53,037 --> 00:20:55,037
Ah! Yes, Your Highness.

322
00:20:55,037 --> 00:20:56,187
I understand.

323
00:20:56,187 --> 00:20:57,867
Forgive me, Your Highness.

324
00:20:57,867 --> 00:21:00,707
I... I am truly grateful to you.

325
00:21:02,147 --> 00:21:05,347
Let's go. We'll discuss 
details back in my chambers.

326
00:21:06,067 --> 00:21:07,057
Yes, Your Highness.

327
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:10,737
Miss Anna, I'll leave matters here to you.

328
00:21:10,737 --> 00:21:12,067
Yes, Your Highness.

329
00:21:15,787 --> 00:21:17,667
Your Highness. Your Highness!

330
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:18,607
What is it, Barov?

331
00:21:18,607 --> 00:21:22,357
Your Highness, I understand 
your eagerness to meet this witch.

332
00:21:22,357 --> 00:21:25,617
However, there might be a complication.

333
00:21:25,617 --> 00:21:27,517
Oh? What is it?

334
00:21:27,517 --> 00:21:31,897
You see, this girl's name 
is Nana Pine, right?

335
00:21:31,897 --> 00:21:34,827
The surname Pine doesn't 
belong to commoners.

336
00:21:34,827 --> 00:21:38,627
It belongs to a minor 
noble in town, Baron Pine.

337
00:21:39,557 --> 00:21:40,967
Is that so?

338
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:42,487
Yes, Your Highness.

339
00:21:42,487 --> 00:21:45,727
Nana is indeed the daughter 
of Baron Tigui Pine.

340
00:21:47,977 --> 00:21:49,937
If the nobles find out, 
it could be troublesome.

341
00:21:50,997 --> 00:21:54,327
Mr. van Bate, bring Nana 
here tomorrow morning.

342
00:21:54,327 --> 00:21:55,847
Come at the usual lesson time.

343
00:21:55,847 --> 00:21:56,837
Don't draw attention.

344
00:21:56,837 --> 00:21:58,057
Yes, Your Highness.

345
00:21:58,627 --> 00:22:01,447
Barov, once Nana arrives tomorrow,

346
00:22:01,447 --> 00:22:02,917
take her directly to the kitchen.

347
00:22:02,917 --> 00:22:04,677
Clear the area beforehand.

348
00:22:04,677 --> 00:22:06,167
I'll meet her in the kitchen.

349
00:22:06,697 --> 00:22:09,397
Very wise, Your Highness.

350
00:22:39,837 --> 00:22:41,067
Your Highness.

351
00:22:41,587 --> 00:22:42,857
Miss Pine is here.

352
00:22:53,257 --> 00:22:54,457
It's all right.

353
00:22:55,867 --> 00:22:57,817
Go on, Nana.

354
00:22:58,327 --> 00:22:59,747
Greet His Highness.

355
00:23:01,857 --> 00:23:03,387
H-Hello.

356
00:23:03,387 --> 00:23:07,027
I-I'm Nana Pine, Your Highness.

357
00:23:07,957 --> 00:23:09,877
Hello, Miss Pine.

358
00:23:11,047 --> 00:23:13,027
Welcome. Please have a seat.

359
00:23:20,717 --> 00:23:22,967
Go on, it's fine.

360
00:23:22,967 --> 00:23:24,927
His Highness is asking you to sit.

361
00:23:24,927 --> 00:23:26,547
Go ahead, it's all right.

362
00:23:26,547 --> 00:23:27,147
Go on.

363
00:23:27,147 --> 00:23:28,027
Miss Pine,

364
00:23:28,847 --> 00:23:30,727
may I also call you Nana?

365
00:23:31,687 --> 00:23:33,027
Here is some food.

366
00:23:33,027 --> 00:23:35,047
I hope you like it.

367
00:24:07,287 --> 00:24:08,027
Nana.

368
00:24:11,667 --> 00:24:13,797
Sister Anna!

369
00:24:17,217 --> 00:24:20,457
Thank goodness! Sister Anna, you're alive!

370
00:24:20,457 --> 00:24:22,167
They all said you were dead,

371
00:24:22,167 --> 00:24:24,587
but I knew they were lying.

372
00:24:26,957 --> 00:24:29,017
I've missed you so much.

373
00:24:31,777 --> 00:24:33,577
Your Highness, time is short.

374
00:24:33,577 --> 00:24:35,497
I must return to the 
construction site immediately.

375
00:24:35,497 --> 00:24:37,837
I will never fail to 
meet your expectations.

376
00:24:38,387 --> 00:24:41,627
Anna and Nana... 
I entrust them to your care.

377
00:24:43,687 --> 00:24:45,437
So delicious, Sister Anna!

378
00:24:44,487 --> 00:24:45,437
Nana.

379
00:24:47,077 --> 00:24:49,127
I heard from Professor Karl

380
00:24:49,127 --> 00:24:51,277
that you've also awakened as a witch.

381
00:24:54,207 --> 00:24:55,807
When did it start?

382
00:24:56,277 --> 00:24:57,777
How did you discover it?

383
00:24:58,347 --> 00:24:59,667
Could you tell me about it?

384
00:25:02,847 --> 00:25:05,427
About a week ago,

385
00:25:05,427 --> 00:25:07,647
I saw a little bird with a broken leg,

386
00:25:07,647 --> 00:25:09,387
and I really wanted to help it.

387
00:25:09,387 --> 00:25:14,307
Then, I felt something 
flow out from my palm,

388
00:25:14,307 --> 00:25:16,427
like a ball of sticky water,

389
00:25:16,427 --> 00:25:18,107
and it enveloped the bird.

390
00:25:18,107 --> 00:25:19,157
Oh?

391
00:25:19,797 --> 00:25:20,847
And then?

392
00:25:21,287 --> 00:25:22,897
Then...

393
00:25:22,897 --> 00:25:24,567
Then the bird was healed!

394
00:25:26,047 --> 00:25:27,097
Carter.

395
00:25:27,097 --> 00:25:28,567
Oh! Yes, Your Highness?

396
00:25:29,367 --> 00:25:31,007
Go into town immediately.

397
00:25:31,007 --> 00:25:32,727
Find a hunter and buy some small animals—

398
00:25:32,727 --> 00:25:35,767
injured ones, dying ones, and dead ones.

399
00:25:35,767 --> 00:25:37,527
Get a few of each.

400
00:25:37,527 --> 00:25:38,707
Yes, Your Highness.

401
00:25:50,897 --> 00:25:56,297
Nana, could you show me 
that sticky ball of water again?

402
00:25:57,087 --> 00:25:59,507
Don't you want to help them?

403
00:26:00,407 --> 00:26:01,457
Sure.

404
00:26:28,967 --> 00:26:30,407
They're so cute.

405
00:26:32,717 --> 00:26:33,587
Look.

406
00:26:34,797 --> 00:26:36,797
Damaged parts can be healed.

407
00:26:37,397 --> 00:26:39,227
Severed limbs can be perfectly reattached.

408
00:26:40,467 --> 00:26:42,367
But if the limb is lost,

409
00:26:42,367 --> 00:26:44,597
it cannot be regenerated.

410
00:26:45,227 --> 00:26:46,307
And...

411
00:26:47,427 --> 00:26:49,317
death cannot be reversed.

412
00:26:54,437 --> 00:26:57,227
This power is incredible.

413
00:26:58,217 --> 00:27:00,627
Saving lives and healing the 
wounded is a knight's duty.

414
00:27:01,287 --> 00:27:02,867
And yet, it is this little girl

415
00:27:03,467 --> 00:27:06,947
who has shown me what 
healing truly looks like.

416
00:27:06,947 --> 00:27:10,377
I really... don't know what to say.

417
00:27:11,977 --> 00:27:15,187
Your Highness, I'm beginning to 
understand your approach to witches.

418
00:27:15,197 --> 00:27:16,017
Carter.

419
00:27:16,017 --> 00:27:17,097
Yes, Your Highness.

420
00:27:17,527 --> 00:27:19,367
Take her home later.

421
00:27:19,367 --> 00:27:21,887
From now on, find opportunities 
to bring her here every day,

422
00:27:21,887 --> 00:27:23,187
so she can practice her powers.

423
00:27:24,007 --> 00:27:26,337
Why not just keep her here?

424
00:27:26,337 --> 00:27:28,787
Her powers are truly astonishing.

425
00:27:29,617 --> 00:27:30,967
Her family is nobility.

426
00:27:31,687 --> 00:27:34,107
Nana hasn't been exposed as a witch yet.

427
00:27:34,107 --> 00:27:35,977
If we brought her here now,

428
00:27:35,977 --> 00:27:39,057
it might prematurely start a 
conflict with the local nobles.

429
00:27:39,727 --> 00:27:42,917
And we're not ready for that yet.

430
00:27:42,917 --> 00:27:45,527
Your Highness, do you truly believe that

431
00:27:45,527 --> 00:27:49,017
we can survive the Months of Demons here,

432
00:27:49,017 --> 00:27:51,277
with just that wall and 
the power of witches?

433
00:27:51,277 --> 00:27:52,117
Of course.

434
00:27:53,287 --> 00:27:56,257
But this alone won't be enough.

435
00:27:57,797 --> 00:27:59,267
Because besides the demonic beasts,

436
00:28:00,327 --> 00:28:02,237
we have many more enemies.

437
00:28:05,977 --> 00:28:09,647
Translator: Henry Lin
